Selenium CLass 4
================
>> CSS Selectors:
It is another way of locating elements on the web page

Syntax:
tagname[attribute = 'attribute value']
e.g. button[type='Submit']

------
Note: CSS does not give an opportunity to locate the elements by its text.
------

>> Shortcuts for CSS:
 - Shortcut for ClassName --> '.'
   Syntax: tagname.classNameValue
   e.g. input.button

 - Shortcut for ID --> '#'
   Syntax: tagname#IDValue
   e.g. input#usernameTextInput

 - contains() Method in CSS:
   * represents contains method in css
   Syntax: tagname[attribute *='attribute value']
   e.g. input[placeholder*='Email']

 - starts-with method in CSS:
   ^ (Circumflex) symbol represents starts with method
   Syntax: tagname[attribute ^='starting attribute value']
   e.g.

 - ends-with method in CSS:
   $ symbol represents ends-with method in css
   Syntax: tagname[attribute $= 'ending attribute value']
   e.g. img[src$='image.png']

>> Xpath vs CSS:
 - CSS cannot locate the elements by text where Xpath can
 - no ends-with method in Xpath
 - CSS is faster than Xpath (finding elements)
 - CSS has shortcuts which Xpath does not have
 - no advanced CSS shortcuts
 - CSS has more simple syntax than Xpath